        "children": [
          {
            "_key": "mc-ch-en-1-span",
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "The operator was running transport for multiple enterprise contracts, but each account had its own planning habits, service review process, and billing rhythm. That made it hard to maintain one clear operating standard across the business.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_key": "mc-ch-en-2",
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "markDefs": [],
        "children": [
          {
            "_key": "mc-ch-en-2-span",
            "_type": "span",
            "text": "Dispatch teams were resolving service exceptions account by account, while finance teams were closing cycles with fragmented evidence. SLA drift and reconciliation delays became a recurring management issue.",
            "marks": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "_key": "mc-ch-en-3",
        "_type": "block",
        "style": "normal",
        "listItem": "bullet",
